dataElements.name: GEN_ACD_ID
dataElements.description: Please indicate here the identifier of this active case detection activity. It has to be a unique identifier.

dataElements.name: Skin_ACD_Clinic_Lep_PB_T
dataElements.description: Please indicate the number of suspected leprosy cases classified as paucibacillary (PB), i.e. presenting 5 lesions or less. Please note that this classification should be confirmed by skin smear.
dataElements.formName: Number of suspected leprosy cases classified as paucibacillary (PB)

dataElements.name: Skin_ACD_Clinic_Yaws_AZC_T
dataElements.description: Please indicate the number of yaws suspected cases that were treated with azithromycin on site.
dataElements.formName: Number of Yaws suspected cases treated with azithromycin (AZC)

dataElements.name: GEN_Team_Coordinator
dataElements.description: Please indicate the name of the team coordinator

dataElements.name: Skin_ACD_Clinic_Scabies_T
dataElements.description: Please indicate the number of people who meet the case definition for Scabies.

dataElements.name: Skin_ACD_Clinic_Lep_MB_T
dataElements.description: Please indicate the number of suspected leprosy cases classified as multibacillary (MB), i.e. presenting more than 5 lesions. Please note that this classification should be confirmed by skin smear.
dataElements.formName: Number of suspected leprosy cases classified as multibacillary (MB)

dataElements.name: Skin_ACD_Clinic_LF_T
dataElements.description:
Please indicate the number of people who meet the case definition for lymphatic filariasis (LF).
Please also note that any LF suspected case has to be referred to the closest reference center for diagnosis confirmation and case management.
dataElements.formName: Number of suspected lymphatic filariasis cases

dataElements.name: GEN_PLACE_Village_Chief_Text_T
dataElements.description: Please indicate the name of the chief of the village/community
dataElements.formName: Name of the chief of the village/community

dataElements.name: Skin_ACD_Clinic_Yaws_RDT_done_T
dataElements.description: Please indicate the number of yaws suspected cases that you were able to test with Rapid Diagnostic tests
dataElements.formName: Number of Yaws suspected cases tested with Rapid Diagnostic Test (RDT)

dataElements.name: Skin_ACD_Clinic_Other_Specify_T
dataElements.shortName: Please list the other potential diagnosis
dataElements.description: Please list the other potential diagnosis
dataElements.formName: Please list the other potential diagnosis

dataElements.name: GEN_Team_Name_T
dataElements.description: Please indicate the number or the letter which identifies the team that conducted the activity

dataElements.name: Skin_ACD_Pop_Examined_T
dataElements.description: Please indicate the number of people that where clinically examined during this activity

dataElements.name: Skin_ACD_Clinic_CL_T
dataElements.description:
Please indicate the number of people who meet the case definition for cutaneous leishmaniasis (CL). Please note that WHO defines a CL suspected case as a person living in or having travelled to CL-endemic areas showing typical CL skin lesions (macula, plaque, nodule, ulcer).
Please also note that any CL suspected case has to be referred to the closest reference center for diagnosis confirmation and case management.
dataElements.formName: Number of suspected cutaneous leishmaniasis cases

dataElements.name: GEN_Team_Supervisor
dataElements.description: Please indicate the name of the team supervisor

dataElements.name: Skin_ACD_Clinic_Yaws_T
dataElements.description:
Please indicate the number of people who meet the case definition for Yaws. Please note that WHO defines a suspected yaws case as a person with a history of residence in an yaws-endemic area (past or present) who presents with clinically active yaws.
All suspected yaws cases should be tested with rapid tests and treated with azithromycin tablets.
Please fill the Yaws register for all suspected yaws cases

dataElements.name: GEN_Comments_T
dataElements.description: Please indicate here any additional comments

dataElements.name: Skin_ACD_Clinic_Yaws_RDT_positive_T
dataElements.description: Please indicate the number of yaws suspected cases that were positive for Rapid Diagnostic tests, i.e. for whom 2 lines were visible
dataElements.formName: Number of Yaws suspected cases tested positive to Rapid Diagnostic Test (RDT)

dataElements.name: Skin_ACD_Pop_Target_T
dataElements.description: Please indicate the targeted population for this activity, e.g. population of the village, number of pupils of the school...

dataElements.name: Skin_ACD_Clinic_Other_T
dataElements.description: Please indicate the number of people presenting skin lesions, but with another clinical diagnosis.
dataElements.formName: Number of people with skin lesions but another clinical diagnosis

dataElements.name: Skin_ACD_School_YN
dataElements.description: Please click "yes" if the active case detection activity was based in a school and targeting its pupils and eventually teachers. Otherwise, click "no".

dataElements.name: Skin_ACD_Clinic_Lep_T
dataElements.description:
Please indicate the number of people who meet the case definition for leprosy.
Please note that WHO defines a leprosy suspected case as a patient having one or more of the following: 1) Hypo-pigmented skin lesions with loss of sensation; 2) Impairment or involvement of the peripheral nerves as demonstrated by a) definite loss of sensation or b) weakness of hands/feet or face c) autonomic function disorders like anhidrosis; 3) Presence of visible deformities; 4) Signs of the disease with demonstrated presence of Bacilli or histopathological confirmation AND  in need of leprosy treatment as decided by a clinician.

Please also note that any leprosy suspected case has to be referred to the closest reference center for further assessment and case management.

dataElements.name: Skin_ACD_Clinic_SkinLesions_T
dataElements.description: Please indicate, among the people examined, how many people were presenting skin lesions (any kind)
dataElements.formName: Number of people with skin lesions

dataElements.name: Skin_ACD_Clinic_Oncho_T
dataElements.description:
Please indicate the number of people who meet the case definition for Onchocersiasis.
Please also note that any Onchocersiasis suspected case has to be referred to the closest reference center for diagnosis confirmation and case management.

dataElements.name: GEN_School_Director_T
dataElements.description: Please indicate the name of the director of the school (or referent teacher)
dataElements.formName: Name of the Director of the school

dataElements.name: Skin_ACD_Clinic_BU_T
dataElements.description:
Please indicate the number of people who meet the case definition for Buruli ulcer. Please note that WHO defines a BU suspected case as any person with painless nodule, papule, plaque or oedema evolving into a painless ulcer with undermined edges, often leading to invalidating sequelae in an endemic area.
Please also note that any BU suspected case has to be referred to the closest reference center for diagnosis confirmation and case management.
dataElements.formName: Number of Buruli ulcer suspected cases
